Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.09,0:00:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kogorou and I accompanied Ran\Nand Sonoko as they went shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.71,0:00:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But later, we discovered the body of a strangled woman in a park restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.94,0:00:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim, who had dressed in goth\Nloli fashion, was Kuze Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.19,0:00:18.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who we'd seen at a teahouse in Shinjuku prior to her death.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.74,0:00:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon after Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was seated...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.32,0:00:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went to the restroom outside the store before ordering.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.79,0:00:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, Shoudou Yuika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a friend who\Nwas meeting with Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, arrived there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.83,0:00:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never returned to her seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.59,0:00:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shoudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was counted as one of the suspects, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.80,0:00:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her alibi was perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.18,0:00:44.19,Signs,,0,0,0,,Park Restroom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.18,0:00:44.19,Signs,,0,0,0,,Teahouse
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.34,0:00:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.65,0:00:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Flowers dance to the piano's rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.44,0:00:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two people face-to-face is a mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.32,0:00:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The goth loli case is about to be solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.36,0:00:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pay attention to Ran and Sonoko's cosplay too!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.66,0:01:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.53,0:01:02.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.53,0:01:04.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.97,0:02:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did this woman who came here first order anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.60,0:02:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.14,0:03:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although, before she left for the restroom, she did look at the menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.02,0:03:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, would you mind lending us the menu?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:07.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.03,0:03:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think you'll find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mihiro's fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.25,0:03:14.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I accidentally knocked over a glass of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:16.34,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,When I went to pick it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.13,0:03:16.34,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shoudou Yuika (26)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.91,0:03:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I carelessly put the menu down on the\Nsoaked table, so I wiped it off later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.71,0:03:27.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, I also wiped the table and the sofa that got wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.68,0:03:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there should be no trace left showing Mihiro had been here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.51,0:03:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean I will be made out to be the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.81,0:03:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.77,0:03:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.40,0:03:46.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Mihiro's glass already fell to the floor and shattered...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.65,0:03:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shattered?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.15,0:03:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it shattered, does that mean you still have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.07,0:03:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That glass!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:55.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.49,0:03:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's in the non-flammable waste bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.00,0:04:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, these are the fragments?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.17,0:04:02.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:05.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the only glass that was broken today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.46,0:04:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll call the investigators to examine it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.55,0:04:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd like...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.72,0:04:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we also go to the store where Mihiro bought the outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.18,0:04:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know the store she was likely to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.64,0:04:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's this person.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:26.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She came to buy it last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.65,0:04:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.78,0:04:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, was she the only one to buy this outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.99,0:04:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These outfits came out yesterday as our store original.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're very popular, and were completely gone by the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.33,0:04:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this person one of the customers who bought one of the outfits?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.46,0:04:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.79,0:04:47.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was impossible for me to buy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.01,0:04:52.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, I was taking a taxi in Fukuoka for business...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.18,0:04:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And talked to her on the phone about the clothes she'd bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.22,0:04:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Fukuoka?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.35,0:04:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.43,0:05:04.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I arrived at Haneda today, and went\Nstraight to that Shinjuku teahouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.31,0:05:05.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go ahead and investigate if you'd like!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.98,0:05:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I was on that plane with my co-workers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.36,0:05:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, she wouldn't have had a chance to buy the outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:19.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, as the most likely culprit, how did she do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.87,0:05:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.62,0:05:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come here for a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.83,0:05:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I borrowed this store's dressing room to change, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.46,0:05:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, there's a murder case going on and\Nyou still took time to change into loli clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess... it's weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.31,0:05:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, it's really cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.94,0:05:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, it's a waste showing it to a brat like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.65,0:05:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you two wearing the same outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.74,0:05:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really are clueless about these things!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.03,0:06:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is one of the current fashion trends...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.46,0:06:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.58,0:06:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints on the broken glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, she has a perfect alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.67,0:06:16.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, are you finally going to let me go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.55,0:06:18.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.06,0:06:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's getting pretty late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.27,0:06:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.56,0:06:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.82,0:06:33.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An unusually clean place?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.44,0:06:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't think there was anything like\Nthat in the stall where the body was.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.91,0:06:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you checked the other stalls?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I haven't done that yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.58,0:06:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the neighboring stall...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.50,0:06:51.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only the toilet paper cover is unusually clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.05,0:06:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:06:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'd like to go home then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.01,0:07:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to let my friends know about Mihiro's death, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.89,0:07:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, we can't let you yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.27,0:07:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.39,0:07:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had an appointment\Nto meet you at the Shinjuku teahouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.94,0:07:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet she didn't wait for you, left for the restroom and never returned...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, for some reason, she was killed in the Harajuku park restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.95,0:07:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't know about that even if you asked me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.41,0:07:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I can say is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.75,0:07:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I entered the teahouse about ten minutes\Nafter Mihiro went to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.71,0:07:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mihiro didn't return for a while,\NI kept calling her cell phone, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.67,0:07:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It never went through.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when it finally did go through...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:46.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who answered was you, Inspector—that's all I can say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.18,0:07:48.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.43,0:07:51.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you still suspecting me of murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.73,0:07:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.15,0:07:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, Shoudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.19,0:08:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't we go over this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.49,0:08:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Shoudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.70,0:08:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'd have to call Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the park after she left for the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.08,0:08:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she'd have to go back to the teahouse after the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.54,0:08:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the teahouse in Shinjuku to the park in Harajuku...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The roundtrip requires at least thirty minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.38,0:08:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for Shoudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to have arrived at\Nthe teahouse ten minutes after Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.09,0:08:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And weren't Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints found on that glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.14,0:08:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From that, it's obvious that Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwas the one who came to the teahouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.56,0:08:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why did Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} touch that glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.86,0:08:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you're given water at a teahouse, it's normal to drink it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.65,0:08:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait, on the glass that this lady dropped and shattered...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.37,0:08:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any lipstick, was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.79,0:08:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} cosplayed goth loli...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.67,0:08:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wore dark colored lipstick, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.21,0:08:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.05,0:09:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.67,0:09:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy, I don't think you know this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.72,0:09:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you get lipstick on the rim of a glass, it's\Nladylike to use your finger to casually wipe it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.64,0:09:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't think there was any trace of lipstick being wiped away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.19,0:09:20.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, maybe when Mihiro was opening\Nher menu, the glass was in the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.65,0:09:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she simply grabbed it and moved it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.70,0:09:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then she left for the restroom without ever drinking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.78,0:09:34.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In fact, I was also trying to put the menu down\Nwhen I knocked over and broke the glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was lucky, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.04,0:09:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the glass broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.30,0:09:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Lucky"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.13,0:09:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, if it hadn't broken...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.09,0:09:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you were asked by the inspector to go to the\Nmurder scene, and you had to leave the teahouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.89,0:09:57.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think the waitress would've picked it up and\Nwashed it, completely removing the fingerprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.36,0:10:01.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, I was wondering why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.65,0:10:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sat on the side where the goth loli lady left the glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.82,0:10:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally, when two people are meeting up,\Nthey sit across from each other, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.00,0:10:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.41,0:10:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you hadn't sat on that side, you wouldn't have broken the glass...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.21,0:10:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.38,0:10:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People can sit wherever they like!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.88,0:10:26.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, even if the shattered glass weren't\Nwashed, it would've been thrown away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.72,0:10:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when it's finally taken away by a garbage\Ntruck and dumped on Dream Island...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.64,0:10:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To dig it up from a mountain of trash...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.81,0:10:33.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,How bothersome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.35,0:10:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just how many officers do you thin—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:43.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.82,0:10:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's happening again?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.61,0:10:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "Mouri"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.95,0:10:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean Sleeping Kogorou?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.49,0:10:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I won't allow this case to continue sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.25,0:10:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll proceed to explain things in a logical manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.17,0:11:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who strangled Kuze Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nin the Harajuku park restroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.13,0:11:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And traveled by foot to the Shinjuku\Nteahouse and artfully devised an alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.47,0:11:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shoudou Yuika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.01,0:11:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.31,0:11:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hold on, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.77,0:11:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you just say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.15,0:11:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That it would take thirty minutes to get to and come\Nback from the park's restroom to the teahouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.49,0:11:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could Shoudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} get to the teahouse ten\Nminutes after Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left for the restroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.83,0:11:41.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Certainly, that would be impossible if the murder\Ntook place after Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left for the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.50,0:11:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But suppose the murder took place before\NMihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came to the teahouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.30,0:11:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it is then possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.01,0:11:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before she came to the teahouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.72,0:11:54.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the one who appeared there was actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.31,0:11:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.43,0:12:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, I believe you felt the same\Nwhen you saw Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.56,0:12:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The goth loli fashion is rather loud and gaudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.73,0:12:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It left a strong first impression on the teahouse\Nemployee and on those of us who were there...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.91,0:12:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So strong that we couldn't recognize her face clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would've thought that the office lady who\Nentered the teahouse ten minutes later...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.92,0:12:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was in fact the same as the goth loli herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.46,0:12:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of nonsense is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.97,0:12:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say the fingerprints on the\Nglass from the teahouse were Mihiro's?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.18,0:12:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.10,0:12:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because that glass was one you had stolen from that store earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.40,0:12:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.77,0:12:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you invited Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to your home...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.40,0:12:56.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And gave her a drink from that glass, so that\NMihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints would be on the glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.16,0:13:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you arrived by dressing up as\Na goth loli, and were given a glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.87,0:13:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you had to do was switch the glass with the one in\Nyour purse that was covered in Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:13.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ten minutes later, you returned with your\Nmakeup removed and clothes changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.01,0:13:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the reason why you sat on the same\Nside of the table as you did earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.22,0:13:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to purposely knock over the glass you had switched...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.23,0:13:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to have it shatter on the floor and spill water everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wiped off the seat that you sat in ten minutes prior.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.61,0:13:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, we didn't find it odd that there\Nwere no traces of Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sitting in that seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made the broken glass the only\Nevidence that Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you shattered the glass, you picked the shards up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.96,0:13:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you left your fingerprints on the glass while\Nyou made the switch, you now had an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.59,0:13:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you just said that they might be thrown away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.26,0:13:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'd only be the case if Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body\Nwere discovered after two or three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.01,0:14:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.60,0:14:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you called Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} so many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.27,0:14:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she stayed in the stall without coming out even as her\Nphone kept ringing, someone would no doubt check inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.82,0:14:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the more if it happened to be when\Nthe park restroom was crowded.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.45,0:14:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once the body was discovered, the police would\Nsuspect your calling Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} so many times...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.95,0:14:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And would then check the teahouse where you had been.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.04,0:14:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police would then find the shattered glass\Nbefore it was sent away as non-flammable waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.92,0:14:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.51,0:14:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you forgetting something?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.63,0:14:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The goth outfit Mihiro wore was bought\Nby herself from this shop last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.18,0:14:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, it was only being sold yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.73,0:14:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was on a business trip in Fukuoka and\Ndidn't return here until noon today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.90,0:14:51.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have bought it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.27,0:14:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The question isn't who bought it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.53,0:14:57.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead: How many were bought?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss, did Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} buy only one outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she bought two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.54,0:15:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said that she could only come in the evening, and\Nasked me to reserve two outfits of the same size for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The outfits were going fast as interest has been\Nhigh since they were announced a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.80,0:15:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet right after the inspector confirmed with the clerk that\NMihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came by herself to buy the outfit, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.73,0:15:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, was she the only one to buy this outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.60,0:15:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You interrupted, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.36,0:15:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it not so you could ask your question before the clerk\Ncould mention Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had purchased two of the outfits?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.74,0:15:47.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did that in order to change the topic to who\Nbought the outfit, and not how many she bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.31,0:15:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.42,0:15:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.46,0:15:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get that Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shoudou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wear the same size...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.88,0:16:02.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she asked Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to buy an outfit for\Nher and to bring it to their date today. but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the crime, it would take an awful long time to fix her\Nclothes, makeup, and hair to be exactly like Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.77,0:16:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that interfere with her alibi setup?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.27,0:16:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't like the two of them decided to\Ncome dressed the same prior to the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.11,0:16:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.99,0:16:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.28,0:16:26.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And perhaps she bought two outfits all for herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.49,0:16:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she really liked it, and kept a spare in case one got dirty!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.33,0:16:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.21,0:16:33.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't there people who do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.08,0:16:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.09,0:16:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.26,0:16:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's have the girls come and explain it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.64,0:16:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.64,0:16:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you sneak off and hide?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.68,0:16:47.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.81,0:16:48.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.52,0:16:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle told you to hurry out and show us those cute clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.23,0:16:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess it can't be helped!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.19,0:17:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ta-daaa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.36,0:17:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with those looks?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you're wearing the same outfit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.53,0:17:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's called the twin fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.29,0:17:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twin fashion?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.25,0:17:15.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Close friends choose to dress in the same clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.25,0:17:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also keep the same hairstyle, makeup, and handbags.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.92,0:17:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a fashion in which the two look like twins!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.01,0:17:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I thought for sure that Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was\Nalso trying out the twin fashion with her friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.26,0:17:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.64,0:17:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made the suggestion to dress like that to Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.98,0:17:35.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, right after going to that park restroom to change clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.69,0:17:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You proceeded to strangle and kill Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.48,0:17:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.99,0:17:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're naming me as a suspect, why don't you show me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.82,0:17:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The proof that I did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We do have evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.79,0:17:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's on your left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.00,0:17:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were going to look at your watch a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.21,0:17:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you gave up and checked your cell phone clock instead, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.38,0:18:07.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason you hesitated is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.01,0:18:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were strangling Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, she\Nmost likely left scratch marks on your left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.69,0:18:17.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do see wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.23,0:18:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.19,0:18:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did this myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.69,0:18:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.86,0:18:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may talk your way out of those wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.99,0:18:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it appears that no bits of skin were\Ndiscovered on Mihiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingertips.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.12,0:18:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it was her fake nails that created the scratches.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.04,0:18:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be impossible to prove if the nails were disposed of.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.33,0:18:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, instead of setting up your alibi and\Nleaving the scene as soon as possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used remover to completely strip\Nthe fake nails from both of her hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.35,0:18:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.56,0:18:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because you wanted to hide the fact that you were scratched!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.31,0:19:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as your blood while you were strangling her...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.82,0:19:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That came from your wounds and\Ndropped onto a certain place in the stall!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.45,0:19:09.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, what certain place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.91,0:19:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that, Detective Takagi should contact you shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.54,0:19:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megure speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.29,0:19:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.25,0:19:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the next stall, you found traces of blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.80,0:19:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the toilet paper cover was the only place not covered in dust...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.01,0:19:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forensics investigated it and got a luminol reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.97,0:19:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.97,0:19:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the results of the blood tests?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.10,0:19:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not a match to our victim's blood,\Nso it may actually be the culprit's.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the crime actually happened in this stall...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.53,0:19:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the culprit's blood dripped onto the cover,\Ncausing them to move the body to the next stall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.20,0:19:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.37,0:19:57.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I'd like to take a sample of your blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.25,0:20:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take whatever you want if you must.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.08,0:20:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mihiro has already taken everything from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.46,0:20:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't even get my nose to bleed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.63,0:20:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taken... you mean like your boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.47,0:20:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.35,0:20:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first man she took was when I was 20 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.77,0:20:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in a slump...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was one thing after another, I had lost my job...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.10,0:20:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Been driven away from my apartment, and had\Nall my friends leave me for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.69,0:20:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, all that was left was my childhood friend, Mihiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.49,0:20:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through Mihiro, I got a job at her parent's company...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.33,0:20:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she suggested that I live with her in her apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.25,0:20:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather than taking from you, it sounds like she\Nwas a great friend that helped you tremendously!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:47.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.67,0:20:50.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought until recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.67,0:20:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until I found out that losing my job, being kicked out\Nof my apartment, and my friends disappearing...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.31,0:20:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.39,0:21:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all secretly Mihiro's doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.60,0:21:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would she...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.02,0:21:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.23,0:21:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she wanted to make sure that I stuck with her forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.15,0:21:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was also her only friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.11,0:21:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.24,0:21:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was betrayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.49,0:21:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I trusted her!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.91,0:21:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.50,0:21:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time I was the one doing the taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.63,0:22:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two should also cherish those fairytale-like feelings of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.14,0:23:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing as unreliable and fragile as friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.06,0:23:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, let's talk at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.48,0:23:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you an idiot!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.35,0:23:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what if friendship is unreliable and fragile!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.94,0:23:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, when you communicate with\Nyour heart, you can feel warmth inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.94,0:23:19.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were as hard as some chattering iron plate...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't feel that warmth, y'know!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.29,0:23:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.25,0:23:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I had spoken to her the way you did...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.59,0:23:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We may have rekindled that warmth...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.76,0:23:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From so long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.18,0:23:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko, how cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.39,0:23:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Respect!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.06,0:23:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't act so wild in those pretty clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.44,0:23:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.65,0:23:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.52,0:24:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.84,0:24:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scent of almond...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.68,0:24:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.53,0:24:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was is cyanide poisoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.16,0:24:12.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.52,0:24:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We wanted to help with the investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.52,0:24:17.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Mayu was my look-like who died in the landslide?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.36,0:24:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta, what's with that flashlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.04,0:24:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.77,0:24:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.92,0:24:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drink bottle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.84,0:24:49.44,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look Forward to the Next Episode
